  "text": "TLS is enforced across all external interfaces of the Prometheus monitoring stack through HTTPClientConfig from prometheus/common/config. The key findings are:\n\n**Configuration Definition (config/config.go):**\nAll major external interface configurations use HTTPClientConfig, which includes TLS settings:\n- ScrapeConfig (line 830): HTTPClientConfig for scrape targets\n- RemoteWriteConfig (line 1434): HTTPClientConfig for remote write endpoints\n- RemoteReadConfig (line 1597): HTTPClientConfig for remote read endpoints\n- AlertmanagerConfig (line 1305): HTTPClientConfig for Alertmanager endpoints\n- TracingConfig (line 1165): TLSConfig for OTLP tracing exporters\nEach config structure implements SetDirectory and validation methods to properly load and validate TLS certificates and keys.\n\n**Scrape Targets (scrape/scrape.go):**\nThe newScrapeClient function (line 2260) uses config_util.NewClientFromConfig with HTTPClientConfig to create HTTP clients for all scrape targets, ensuring TLS is applied.\n\n**Remote Storage Endpoints (storage/remote/client.go):**\nNewReadClient function (line 151) and related write client initialization use config_util.NewClientFromConfig with HTTPClientConfig to create HTTP clients for both remote read and remote write endpoints.\n\n**Tracing Exporters (tracing/tracing.go):**\nThe getClient function (line 179) explicitly handles TLS for OTLP exporters:\n- For gRPC: Uses otlptracegrpc.WithTLSCredentials with credentials created from TracingConfig.TLSConfig (line 193)\n- For HTTP: Uses otlptracehttp.WithTLSClientConfig with TracingConfig.TLSConfig (line 226)\nThe buildTracerProvider function ensures TLS configuration is applied when installing new tracer providers.\n\n**Web Server (web/web.go, cmd/prometheus/main.go):**\nThe web server uses toolkit_web.ServeMultiple (web.go line with listener setup) which handles TLS via the web configuration file (--web.config.file flag). The exporter-toolkit library manages TLS certificates for the Prometheus web interface.\n\n**Service Discovery Plugins (discovery/ directory):**\nAll service discovery implementations use HTTPClientConfig:\n- AWS plugins (ec2.go, ecs.go, elasticache.go, lightsail.go, msk.go) call config.NewClientFromConfig\n- Cloud providers (azure.go, digitalocean.go, linode.go, vultr.go, etc.) use config.NewClientFromConfig or config.NewRoundTripperFromConfig\n- Orchestration platforms (kubernetes.go, nomad.go, marathon.go, docker.go, dockerswarm.go) apply HTTPClientConfig\n- Others (consul.go, eureka.go, puppetdb.go, http.go, xds/client.go) all use HTTPClientConfig\nThese ensure TLS is enforced for all service discovery HTTP requests.\n\n**Alertmanager Notifications (notifier/alertmanagerset.go):**\nAlertmanager client creation uses HTTPClientConfig from the AlertmanagerConfig structure, ensuring TLS for notification delivery.\n\nThe entire architecture delegates TLS enforcement to HTTPClientConfig from prometheus/common/config, which is validated during configuration loading. The SetDirectory methods in config/config.go handle proper path resolution for certificate and key files. All external interfaces use the same configuration validation chain, ensuring consistent TLS enforcement across scrape targets, remote endpoints, service discovery, tracing exporters, and the web server."
}

